# Phase 106 G2-01 — screenshot-capture mode flag.
#
# To capture store screenshots, copy this file to `.env.screenshot` and load it
# before running `npm run dev` or `npm run build`:
#
#   cp .env.screenshot.example .env.screenshot
#   export $(grep -v '^#' .env.screenshot | xargs)
#   npm run build
#
# When VITE_SCREENSHOT_MODE is truthy, `src/api.ts` returns deterministic demo data
# (DEMO_BRIEF / DEMO_AFFIRMATION / DEMO_SUMMARY) instead of calling the API. This
# lets Plan 05 produce reproducible PNGs for the Even Hub store listing.
#
# SECURITY — DO NOT set VITE_SCREENSHOT_MODE in `.env.production`.
# Vite statically replaces import.meta.env.VITE_* at build time. If this flag is
# ever set in a production build, demo data ships to real store users (T8-leak-1).
# Verify with: `! grep -q VITE_SCREENSHOT_MODE .env.production`

VITE_SCREENSHOT_MODE=1
